casebody.data:
Argued and submitted March 3, (CC 88-3702; CA A61071; SC S39240) 847 P2d 408 Nancy G. Neslund, of Neslund and Neslund, Salem, argued the cause for petitioners on review. With her on the petition were Clayton C. Patrick and William D. Brandt, Salem. Also on the reply brief was Callaghan, Neslund, Neslund & Wilkes, Salem. Before Peterson, Presiding Justice, and Gillette, Van Hoomissen, Fadeley, Unis, and Graber, Justices. MEMORANDUM OPINION

review dismissed as improvidently allowed March 25,1993

Leonard DAVENPORT and Katie Davenport, husband and wife, Respondents on Review, v. Matthew GRUBER and Alice Gruber, husband and wife, Petitioners on Review.

Michael J. Bandonis, of Minor & Boone, P.C., Newport, filed the response and argued the cause for respondents on review.

David B. Williams, Lane County Office of Legal Counsel, Eugene, filed a brief in behalf of amicus curiae Association of Oregon Counties.
